# Frontend conventions

## TypeScript
- No `any`. Use proper generics or `unknown` + narrowing.
- Shared types/interfaces used across features go in `src/types/*`, not inside page modules.
- Services (`src/services/*`) must NOT import types from `src/pages/*`; import from `src/types/*` instead.

## React components
- Functional components + hooks only.
- Use early returns (guard clauses) to reduce nesting.
- If a component exceeds ~150 lines, extract logic into a custom hook or break into sub-components.
- Avoid inline anonymous functions in JSX props for non-trivial components; define stable handlers instead.

## Navigation / interactive elements
- Never nest interactive elements (`<a>` inside `<a>`, `<button>` inside `<a>`).
- Use shadcn `asChild` so the intended element (e.g. `NavLink`) becomes the rendered interactive node.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging (never interpolate `null` into className strings).

## Data fetching
- Use TanStack React Query for all remote data.
- Query keys must be consistent arrays: `["entity"]` for lists, `["entity", id]` for detail.
- Mutations must invalidate the matching query keys on success.

## Forms
- Use `react-hook-form` + `zod` for validation on substantive forms (create/edit flows, multi-field validation).
- Simple search/filter controls (e.g. table filters, assign-dialog lookup) may use controlled inputs + debounced queries without RHF/Zod.
- Reusable form components (`FormComp`, `SelectInput`) must not hardcode field names.

## Logging / debugging
- No `console.log` in committed code. Remove debug logs before completing a task.

## Formatting
- Single Prettier config: `.prettierrc.json` (2 spaces, double quotes, no semicolons, trailing commas ES5, tailwind class sorting via plugin).
- No duplicate config files.
